## Non-negotiables
- No `var`; use `const` / `let` only
- No class components
- No `any` without explicit approval
- Split functions longer than ~40 lines
- Comments explain WHY, not WHAT

```ts
// ❌ any
const parse = (data: any) => data.name

// ✅ unknown + narrowing
const parse = (data: unknown): string => {
  if (typeof data === 'object' && data !== null && 'name' in data) {
    return (data as { name: string }).name
  }
  throw new Error('Invalid data')
}

// ❌ 40+ line god function
function handleSubmit() { /* ...80 lines... */ }

// ✅ split into steps
function handleSubmit() {
  const data = validateForm()
  const result = submitToAPI(data)
  showFeedback(result)
}
```

## Naming
- Components: PascalCase
- Functions / variables: camelCase
- Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE
- Files: PascalCase.tsx for components; kebab-case.ts otherwise

## Types
- Define Props at the top of the same file as the component
- Omit types when inference is clear
- Prefer `type` over `interface` unless you need `extends`

## Formatting (Prettier owns this)
- 2-space indent
- Single quotes
- No semicolons
